                                    oc:blockType "paragraph" ;
                                    oc:contentOrder 11 ;
                                    oc:textContent "The concise version assumes Claude knows what PDFs are and how libraries work." ],
                                [ a oc:Paragraph ;
                                    oc:blockType "paragraph" ;
                                    oc:contentOrder 3 ;
                                    oc:textContent "Not every token in your Skill has an immediate cost. At startup, only the metadata (name and description) from all Skills is pre-loaded. Claude reads SKILL.md only when the Skill becomes relevant, and reads additional files only as needed. However, being concise in SKILL.md still matters: once Claude loads it, every token competes with conversation history and other context." ],
                                [ a oc:Paragraph ;
                                    oc:blockType "paragraph" ;
                                    oc:contentOrder 1 ;
                                    oc:textContent "The [context window](https://platform.claude.com/docs/en/build-with-claude/context-windows) is a public good. Your Skill shares the context window with everything else Claude needs to know, including:" ],
                                [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                                    oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                                    oc:codeContent """## Extract PDF text

PDF (Portable Document Format) files are a common file format that contains
text, images, and other content. To extract text from a PDF, you'll need to
use a library. There are many libraries available for PDF processing, but we
recommend pdfplumber because it's easy to use and handles most cases well.
First, you'll need to install it using pip. Then you can use the code below...
""" ;
